		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Short version: Low delay and AC are priorities.<br><br>Long: Getting the lowest delay weapons is key to quickly improving your melee skills. Maxed melee skills are vital to get the most out of that 47 delay weapon you'll be swaggering around with at 39th level with your newly memmed Greater Heal spell. For now, just getting sub-25 delay, non-rusty weapons makes a nice difference. At 9th level, I'm paying for just starting 2hb which is a slower class of weapons to add to my misery. As I level now, I immediately increase each maxed skill level to its new high while hunting blues. Once those are up, I equip with those weapons to hunt whites and yellows (lay hands renders them blues), or I work on another weapon skill against mobs that do minimal damage so the 'training sessions' are longer ;-). <br><br>Note: admittedly, training when out the window once I was within 2 bubs of those wonderful spells =).<br><br>AC is important so you survive your training until you're ready to solo those nasty, evil hill giants. Always upgrade if you can - you can go back if you don't like the change &lt;chuckle&gt;. Look for DEX and AGI pluses as these increase your chances to hit and not be hit, respectively.<br><br>Spells at 9th will not run you more than 4 or 5 gp each, but 15th spells will be 3-5pp each and so on; save up or die wishing you had... I put Light Heal and Yaulp with my melee, range, taunt, and bash hotkeys. Also, I put my best healing spell on the same key for all of my characters. It makes a difference when the other casters end up #1 on the mob's hate list.<br><br>Good Hunting!<br><br>Olly<br>Holy Knight of Kaladim, 9th Season<br>&lt;&lt;&lt; Your Guild Name Here =) &gt;&gt;&gt;<br>Rodcet Nife</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mlr>
